contentrichtext.text: {{See also|Yang (surname)|Lü (surname)|Yeoman}} '''Yeo''' is the common [[Hong Kong]] Chinese surname (楊) [[Yang (surname)|Yang]]. It is sometimes spelt as '''Yeoh''' or '''Yio'''. <br>'''Yeo''' is the [[Korean language|Korean]] surname from [[Chinese language|Chinese]] surname [[Lu (surname)|Lu]] (呂), etc. <br>'''Yeo''' may also be an [[English language|English]] surname, derived from the word "[[Yeoman]]" ==People== * [[Brian Yeo]] (born 1944), English former footballer * [[Douglas Yeo]] (born 1955), American symphony trombonist and professor *[[Gary Yeo]], a Singaporean sprinter * [[George Yeo]] (born 1954), Singaporean former politician and Air Force brigadier-general * [[Gwendoline Yeo]] (born 1977), Singaporean-born American actress and niece of George Yeo * [[Iva Yeo]] (born 1939), Canadian politician * [[James Lucas Yeo]] (1782-1818), British naval commander who served in the War of 1812 *
